ABOUT
/$
$
​
The North Beaches Art Walk (NBAW) got its start in 2007 when Beaches art-industry professionals JoAnne Adams, Alice Gartland, and Linda Stewart came together in hopes of recreating the popular art walk atmosphere of Downtown Jacksonville. Through their nurturing and dedication, the event grew considerably.
The NBAW is a free event held on the third Thursday of each month from 5-9 pm. Featuring many local visual artists and live performers, the streets of the Beaches Town Center - where Atlantic Boulevard meets the ocean - erupt with creativity and liveliness. What was once a small pool of carefully selected artists has now become a bubbling ocean of art, a place where woodworkers commingle with mixed media designers, and musicians play into the night.
The overall mission of Art Walk is to expose the community to the vast number of local Artists right here at the Beaches. Talent from all over North East Florida shows at the North Beaches Art Walk. With over 50+ participating artists, NBAW is a diverse art destination and shopping experience for the entire family. Local venues in Beaches Town Center set the backdrop for this great monthly destination and community gathering. We welcome locals and out of towners alike, to bring you a communal experience.
​
The North Beaches Art Walk is orchestrated by the North Beaches Art Walk Association, a nonprofit organization 501 (c)(3) based in Atlantic Beach, FL. Since its beginning in October of 2007, the North Beaches Art Walk has continued to receive positive support from the community and has an ever-growing list of participating merchants and artists.
/$
$
WHERE TO FIND US
/$
$
The North Beaches Art Walk is located within the heart of the Beaches Town Center, between Neptune Beach and Atlantic Beach, Florida. Artists and musicians fill the main streets of Atlantic Blvd., Ocean Blvd., and First Street, surrounded by wonderful restaurants and bars.
